{
  "texts": [
    "Thus, building effective deferral models remains a challenge, and human-AI decision-making in this setup needs notable improvements, much like the previous setup.",
    "Including highlights (details on how we do that in Appendix E) reduces recall, contrary to the belief they might provide additional signal about when the model is correct/wrong.",
    "We still aim to provide initial insights into whether explanations for likely-wrong predictions help decision makers, as we hypothesize in §2.",
    "Without workable deferral models, we do not study this in a realistic setup with deferral mistakes; all participants get instances that the model mishandles.",
    "Given the lack of usefulness of explanations so far, we opt for a small-scale study and include a freeform question about how explanations are helpful, if at all."
  ]
}